BUILDING
 There is no configure script nor is there anything to compile.

 Setup the via a make.

  $ make

 Running a `make install` as root will distribute the files to
 the filesystem. The default is to provide a systemd user service.
 Compiling with WITH_OPENRC=1 will provide openrc support and not
 systemd support. You can of course just use old school cron too.

  # make install

If you wish to contribute to other distros, fork this project
on github and submit a pull request:
https://github.com/graysky2/modprobed-db
